	<text>
		<body>
			<div type="entry">
				<pb facs="https://leaf.bucknell.edu/sites/default/files/2026-01/diary74.jpg"/>
				<dateline><date when="1862-06-01">Sunday June 1</date>.</dateline>
				<p>We had a sermon from <persName cert="high" key="Charles Mallory"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper019"
						type="real">Mr. Mallory</persName> in a grove of <objectName type="nature"
						>pines</objectName> and we lounged through the day - <name type="weather">it
						was excessively hot</name> - we put up the <objectName type="equipment"
						>tent</objectName> sides and counted take every breath of air. The pleasant
					places have their annoyances - <objectName type="nature">wood ticks</objectName>
					abound - a <objectName type="nature">reddish brown bug</objectName>, about the
					size of a <objectName type="nature">bed bug</objectName>, which plugs its
						<objectName type="nature/body">nipper</objectName> into the <objectName
						type="body">flesh</objectName> and cant be pulled out, you have to cut them
					off, leaving the <objectName type="nature/body">nipper</objectName> stuck in.
					there are <objectName type="nature">alligators</objectName> in the <placeName
						role="near union regiment" type="creek" cert="medium" key="Slocum Creek"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_gazetteer.xml#linnpl079"
							>creek<precision match="@ref" precision="medium"/></placeName> and these
						<placeName>cypress swamps</placeName>. Whew, what a nice time we’ll have.
				</p>
			</div>
		</body>
	</text>
